Place code 
==========
- LFPO = Paris Orly, France
- LFPG = Paris / Charles De Gaulle, France
- LFLY = Lyon Bron, France
- LFLL = Lyon Satolas, France
- LFML = Marseille, France
- LFQQ = Lille, France
- LFRS = Nantes, France
- LFBD = Bordeaux, France

For the main dataset, 
- we aggregate the temperature of the cities by weighted averaging, proportitional to their annual energy consumption. 

    France Region
  1 Ile-de-France               (Paris)     69k GWh 	
  2 Rhône-Alpes                 (Lyon) 		  65k GWh
  3 Provence-Alpes-Côte-d'Azur  (Marseille) 38k GWh
  4 Nord-Pas-de-Calais          (Lille)     35k GWh
  5 Pays-de-la-Loire            (Nantes)    24k GWh
  6 Aquitaine                   (Bordeaux)  22.5k GWh
  see also: 
    http://www.rte-france.com/uploads/Mediatheque_docs/vie_systeme/annuelles/Statistiques_energie_electrique/an/statistiques_annuelles_2010_an.pdf

- to compute the temperature of Paris, we average both, LFPO and LFPG
- to compute the temperature of Lyon, we average both, LFLY and LFLL

